    {
      "key": "LYLT-356",
      "summary": "*Earn | P1 | CLM Point Source Tracking Management (SF Configuration) Q3 Dependency",
      "status": "Backlog",
      "priority": "High or Should Have",
      "assignee": "Marcus Forbes",
      "labels": [
        "earn_replat",
        "earn_replat_p1"
      ],
      "description_text": "Epic Description\nConfigure and manage the source of points earned. Create a flexible and dynamic framework that can handle various sources of points, such as purchases, promotions, referrals, and more\u2014each with its own set of expiration rules.\nAs a Marriott Bonvoy Member,\nI want to track the source of my points for different transaction types, currencies, and promotions, bonuses, all partners (any way that a member can earn a point)\nso that I can see a detailed and accurate record of my points accumulation from various sources.\nEpic Details\nTrack\u00a0earning of the points from different transaction types, currencies, and promotions \nPoint Categories sources: Points Earned from Stay(Bonvoy Points), Vistana Points, MVW Points(Pre/Post Spinoff), Bonus Points:\nActivity Base Point earn = Stay processing earn, MVW Post Spinoff (Continuous earn, redeemable)\n\nLegacy Historical Points = Vistana, MVW Pre Spinoff/MORI (Redeemable Only, no continuous earn)\n\nFixed Base Point earn = All other processing, service recovery, bonus codes etc.  (Manual Earn posted by MI Associate, redeemable) \nAdd bonus points outside of a stay (permission based access)\n\nRemove bonus points outside of a stay (permission based access)\n\n\nVistana Points\nMarriott Bonvoy Points\nMarriott Vacations Worldwide (Pre-Spinoff)\nMarriott Vacations Worldwide (Post-Spinoff)\nFraud Requirement - All Stay Transactions should have visibility into how they were earned (source or Rule ID) and can be easily extracted. \nAssumptions (if applicable)\nConfigurable for changes - expiry model changes, activity type grouping changes or rules change.\n\n\n\nOut-of-Scope\nBusiness Use Cases (The Life of a Point)\nActivity Based Earn\nStay processing earn\n\n\nFixed base point earn\nBonus codes\n\nPromotions\n\n\n",
